body:
I'm seeing an issue where [xlsx/workbook-writer.commit](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/695023fe6510e1f17d42ff7460fbe5b705e16560/lib/stream/xlsx/workbook-writer.js#L97-L112) doesn't resolve or reject. 

I've added some logging to _finalize
```
  _finalize() {
    console.log('exceljs:_finalize')
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      function fail (error) {
        console.error('exceljs:failing', error);
        reject(error);
      }
      this.stream.on('error', fail);
      this.stream.on('finish', () => {
        console.log('exceljs:_finalize:resolving');
        resolve(this);
      });
      this.zip.on('error', fail);

      console.log('exceljs:zip.finalize');
      this.zip.finalize();
    });
  }
```

Although I see the `exceljs:_finalize` and `exceljs:zip:finalize` messages in logs, I'm not seeing any of the messages logged on `stream.error`, `stream.finish`, or `zip.error` events. Any thoughts as to what might be going on?
